National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with former Lebanese Prime Minister Saad Hariri to discuss various regional issues. Rice thanked Hariri for his efforts in strengthening the partnership between the US and Lebanon and expressed US support for Lebanon and its people. She praised the performance of Lebanese state institutions and security forces and reiterated US commitment to Lebanon's security and sovereignty. Rice emphasized the need for all Lebanese parties to implement the policy of dissociation and support the implementation of relevant UN Security Council resolutions on Lebanon. Rice and Hariri also discussed the importance of finding a political solution in Syria and providing international assistance to Lebanon in hosting Syrian refugees. Rice emphasized the need for Lebanon's parliament to elect a president in accordance with the constitution.